<F P=106> [From the "Danuza" column by Danuza Leao] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Celso Amorim will leave Brazil on 3 
May on a 10-day world tour. Amorim will visit France, where he 
will meet with the French defense minister and the UNESCO 
director general. Later he will represent President Itamar 
Franco at the inauguration of Nelson Mandela. Amorim also will 
visit Mozambique and Angola. 

