<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits Places of Economic Interest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits Places of Economic Interest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2904175994 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 2140 GMT 27 Apr 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2904175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 27 Apr (PL) -- Zambian President Frederick 
Chiluba visited places of economic and social interest in Cuba 
today to strengthen bilateral cooperation, he said. The 
president, on an official and friendly visit to our nation upon 
invitation from his Cuban counterpart, Fidel Castro, visited an 
agricultural cooperative in western Havana Province and 
"Hermanos Ameijeiras" Hospital, one of the country's most 
important. Cuban Health Ministry sources said 22 Cuban 
specialists render their services in that southern Africa 
nation, and we hope to increase that number. 
  The Zambian Government has stated its interest in reaching 
cooperation agreements in the sugar industry and its 
derivatives, the pharmaceutical industry, and the public health 
and sports sectors. 
  Local Foreign Ministry sources have announced plans for the 
construction of a sugar refinery by Cuban technicians, and 
Lusaka will finance all the operations. The exchange of trainers 
in several sport disciplines, such as boxing, soccer, and 
baseball, is also expected. 
  Chiluba was awarded the "Jose Marti" national order, the 
highest distinction granted by the Cuban Government, and he held 
official conversations with Fidel Castro, during which they 
discussed issues dealing with current international politics and 
the situation in Angola. 
  The Zambian delegation will leave for Varadero Beach, 
approximately 100 km east of the capital, tomorrow and will 
travel next Friday to the eastern city of Santiago de Cuba, 
where many young people from this African nation study. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

