<H3> <TI>   Caribbean NGO's Appoint Cuban Spokesman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Caribbean NGO's Appoint Cuban Spokesman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0405004494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1941 GMT 
3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0405004494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the International Small Island States Conference 
being held in Barbados, the Caribbean group of Non-Governmental 
Organizations [NGO] has advocated promoting alternative 
development strategies as well as environmental education. The 
proposals of the Caribbean organizations include giving 
nongovernmental groups a voice in the decision-making process 
regarding sustainable development, and the ratification of 
Accord 169 of the International Labor Organization on the rights 
of indigenous peoples. 
  Other proposals include restructuring military budgets to 
allocate those resources to social services and environmental 
protection. The Caribbean group of Non-Governmental 
Organizations, which is holding sessions parallel to the Small 
Island State Conference, by consensus appointed the Cuban 
delegate as its spokesman. 

</TEXT>

