  [Text] Three political parties in Port-au-Prince 
recommended a vote on the Amnesty Law in order to release the 
country's crisis. They are the Union of Democratic Patriots, led 
by Rockfeller Guerre; Alliance for the Liberation and Progress 
of Haiti, led by Reynold Georges; and the Liaison of Democratic 
Forces, led by Daniel Narcisse. These parties demand the 
resignations of Army Commander in Chief Raoul Cedras, General 
