<DOCNO> FBIS4-56437 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat086_e_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-086 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CENTRAL AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Costa Rica </F>
<H3> <TI>   Asian, NAFTA Exports Up Overall </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Asian, NAFTA Exports Up Overall </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0305185694 </F>
<F P=103> PA0305185694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Paris AFP in Spanish at 1730 GMT on 26 
April reports that despite the overall increase in exports, 
sales to Asia and members of NAFTA decreased by 2 percent during 
the first quarter of the year compared to the same period in 
1993. Exports to the European Union increased by 20 percent, 
and exports to Central America, Costa Rica's third-largest 
trading partner, increased by more than 7 percent higher than 
during the first quarter of 1993. 

</TEXT>

