<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-086 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Approves Series of Constitutional Reforms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Approves Series of Constitutional Reforms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0405023594 San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY in Spanish 30 Apr 
94 p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PA0405023594 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Last night, the Legislative Assembly approved a 
series of constitutional reforms affecting individual rights, 
public health, economic order, and the judicial branch. 
  The reform of Subparagraph 2 of Article 11 establishes that 
a 
person has the right to a writ of habeas corpus when any 
individual or authority illegally or arbitrarily restricts his 
or her liberty. This is also applicable when any authority 
attacks the mental or physical wellbeing of those people 
detained. 
  Modifications to Article 17 state that no government branch, 
official, or authority may use expired procedures in pending 
legal cases or to start legal proceedings against individuals. 
  Regarding health, an amendment to Article 68 establishes 
that 
the Public Health Higher Council shall comprise representatives 
from the fields of medicine, dentistry, pharmacy, veterinary 
medicine, clinical laboratory science, nursing, and psychiatry. 
Congress also reformed Article 120, which now reads: "All 
concessions granted by the state to exploit harbors, railroads, 
canals, or other public holdings require that terms and 
conditions be set while taking into account the nature of the 
projects and the investment required." 
  Regarding distribution of the state budget, the judicial 
branch will be entitled to an annual allotment of not less than 
4 percent of the overall budget. This includes the National 
Judiciary Council and the National Lawyers and Notary Public 
Council. The Prosecutor General's Office, the Attorney 
General's Office, and the Human Rights Ombudsman will together 
have an annual assignment of not less than 2 percent of the 
budget. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-56442 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat086_f_94005" </HT>


