<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Woman Suspected of Stealing Children Found Slain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Woman Suspected of Stealing Children Found Slain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0405000294 Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO in Spanish 3 May 
94 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> PA0405000294 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The body of a woman who appeared to be a foreigner 
and was accused of stealing children was found yesterday along 
the banks of the Cabus River in Malacatan Municipality, San 
Marcos Department. The body showed signs of bruises and machete 
wounds. The body of the woman, who was described as being about 
40 years old and 1.7 meters tall, was found by passersby who 
immediately notified police. 
  The regional judge and National Police arrived at the scene 
and determined that the woman had been murdered several days 
earlier. Because the body was already decomposing, they ordered 
an immediate burial. Her identity remains unknown. 
  Police report that an investigation has begun and that four 
individuals have confessed to killing the woman, who apparently 
was a foreigner. Those arrested were identified as Hector Perez 
Vicente, 21; Valentin Santos, 27; Jesus Martin, 20; and Roberto 
Perez. They confessed to committing the crime because the woman 
was allegedly involved in the theft of children at El Silencio 
ranch, San Marcos Department. 

</TEXT>

