<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Supports Taiwan Rejoining UN </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Supports Taiwan Rejoining UN </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0405092094 Taipei CNA in English 0742 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0405092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Edward Chen] </F>
  [Text] Managua, May 3 (CNA) -- Nicaraguan Foreign Minister 
Ernesto Leal Sanchez Tuesday [3 May] reiterated his country's 
firm support for the Republic of China's [ROC] bid to return to 
the United Nations [UN] . 
  Speaking at a news conference for the ROC press corps in 
advance of President Li Teng-hui's visit, Leal said that the 
international community can not deny the economic strength of 
the ROC and its huge foreign currency reserves. 
  He stressed that the road back to the UN will be difficult 
and fraught with obstacles, but the UN cannot continue to ignore 
the rights of the more than 21 million Chinese people living in 
Taiwan. 
  Leal also said that Nicaragua will strengthen its relations 
with other Asia-Pacific nations, and use the ROC to help in its 
efforts. The ROC left the UN in 1971 after Beijing assumed the 
China seat. 

</TEXT>

