<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clandestine Radio Threatens Americans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clandestine Radio Threatens Americans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0305200994 (Clandestine) Radio Soley Leve in Creole 0300 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0305200994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Soley Leve </F>
<F P=105>  Creole </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ah well, Americans, you have now imposed your FRAPH 
[Revolutionary Front for the Promotion and Progress of Haiti] on 
us. You have found your submissive Army too small for us. 
Americans, you fear that someday we could be furious, that we 
could defeat your Army, and then (?take another direction). You 
are afraid, are you not? You have seen what we can do when we 
are furious. 
  But let me tell you, Americans: Neither your shitty Army nor 
your farting FRAPH will be able to catch us and they will not 
(?try to) catch us because our roots are deeply embedded in the 
soil. 
  (?Our misery has reached its limit; we have reached the 
deadline). If nothing is done, we will act as did Dessalines, we 
will act as did Dessalines, we will act as did Dessalines. 

</TEXT>

