<H3> <TI>   Cultural Agreement Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cultural Agreement Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0405222094 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1949 GMT 
4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0405222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 4 May, Colombian Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin and 
Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina signed the ratification 
of a cultural agreement, dating from 1978, between Colombia and 
Cuba, at the Cuban Foreign Ministry. Sanin and Robaina also 
signed an agreement that standardizes higher education diplomas 
and titles. 
  Before signing these agreements, Sanin visited Casa de las 
Americas, where she donated typical Colombian items to the Latin 
American art exhibit. She also met with Marcia Leyseca, vice 
president of Casa de las Americas, Pablo Milanes, Sintio Vitier, 
Senen Paz, and others. 

</TEXT>

