<H3> <TI>   Grand Front, Socialist Unity To Cooperate on Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grand Front, Socialist Unity To Cooperate on Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0505030994 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1926 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0505030994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 4 May (NA) -- The Grand Front (FG) and 
the Socialist Unity (US) today agreed to create a Political 
Action Commission that will outline a program of cooperation and 
the election strategy for an eventual alliance, with an eye to 
the 1995 elections. 
  In addition, the leaders of the two coalitions decided that 
their members in the Constituent Assembly, which is to be held 
in the cities of Santa Fe and Parana, will work "together," and 
thus the two blocs will hold their first meeting in Congress on 
6 April. 
  The resolutions were adopted during a meeting at FG 
headquarters between the FG and the US. Attending for the FG 
were: Fernando Solanas, Carlos Chacho Alvarez, Patricio 
Echegaray, Marcelo Vensentini, Carlos Auyero, Anibal Ibarra, and 
Mary Sanchez; and for the US: Norberto La Porta, Alfredo Bravo, 
Hector Bravo, Guillermo Estevez Boero, Ernesto Jaimovich, Mario 
Mazitelli, and Jose Seoane. 

</TEXT>

