<H3> <TI>   Army Commander Balza Receives Death Threats </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Commander Balza Receives Death Threats </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0505023294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2235 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0505023294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Buenos Aires, 4 May (NA) -- The family of Army 
Commander Lieutenant General Martin Balza has received death 
threats in an anonymous message that demands that the death of 
conscript Omar Carrasco not be investigated, as "the Neuquen 
case is closed." 
  Pablo Balza, 23, son of the general, today found on the 
windshield of his car a typewritten note in which his father is 
threatened with death and which contained details about the 
family life of the general's children. [passage omitted] 
  Military sources state that this is not the first time that 
Gen. Balza and his family have received death threats. 

</TEXT>

