<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palmeira Chosen as Cardoso's Running Mate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palmeira Chosen as Cardoso's Running Mate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0405123894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0405123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After lengthy internal meetings and conversations, 
the PFL [Liberal Front Party] has designated Alagoas Senator 
Guilherme Palmeira as Fernando Henrique Cardoso's running mate 
for the presidential elections of 3 October. 
  The PFL also considered the designation of Senator Marco 
Maciel, but he declined. 
  The PFL informed Senator Fernando Henrique Cardoso of the 
designation during a lunch. Cardoso was satisfied with the 
designation. He said: 
  [Begin Cardoso recording] It is a good choice because we 
need 
someone from the northeastern region, with political experience, 
with well-known positions, and who will be accepted by the PSDB 
[Brazilian Social Democracy Party]. Guilherme Palmeira meets 
these requirements. In addition, he can help us a lot because 
he is a factor for unity within the PFL, and this is important 
for the electoral contest in the northeastern region. [end 
recording] 
  The PSDB is scheduled to hold its convention on 14 May in 
Contagem, Minas Gerais. The convention will formalize Senator 
Cardoso's designation as presidential candidate. 

</TEXT>

