<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement With Mercosur Bloc Under Preparation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement With Mercosur Bloc Under Preparation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0405231894 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0405231894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Carlos Figueroa said today that 
Chile is putting the finishing touches on an agreement to link 
up with the Common Market of the South, Mercosur. 
  Figueroa explained that Mercosur is seen by the great powers 
and by international investors as one of the most interesting 
centers for investment. Mercosur includes the two largest South 
American countries, Argentina and Brazil, which are Chile's main 
trade partners. 
  [Begin Figueroa recording] In all of the bilateral meetings 
between the Mercosur country presidents and then President 
Patricio Aylwin, and now with President Eduardo Frei, the 
Mercosur countries' interest in having Chile become a member has 
been very clear. [end recording] 
  Figueroa said that the decision regarding Mercosur cannot be 
delayed. He explained, however, that Chile cannot join Mercosur 
as a member due to the high tariff rate of that common market. 
This is why, he said, the Foreign Ministry is preparing a 
formula to reach an agreement with Mercosur as a whole. 

</TEXT>

