<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebels Occupy Giraldo Municipality </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rebels Occupy Giraldo Municipality </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0405130494 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0405130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Luis Alberto Mogollon; from "Caracol's 0600-0900" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Roads remain blocked in Giraldo Municipality, 
western Antioquia Department, not allowing Army troops to 
reinforce the police command that is currently fighting with the 
guerrillas. A Giraldo Municipality official told Caracol the 
following: 
  [Begin unidentified municipality official recording] We 
cannot leave our homes. It all began after midnight, at 0030. 
We cannot see clearly; we cannot step outside the door but we 
can see through the windows and through the crack in the door 
that the main square and the streets are full of guerrillas. We 
are sure that the highway junction, the road between (Manglara) 
and Uraba is blocked. [Words indistinct] at the command and the 
police have been unable to leave. The guerrillas are gathered 
at the entrance into town. [end recording] 
  The Antioquia Department Government will analyze the public 
order situation at a Security Council meeting this morning. 

</TEXT>

