<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 13 April 
1994 on page 10 reports that the National Institute for Agrarian 
Reform (INRA) is planning to issue land ownership titles for 27 
farms totaling 6,545 manzanas in the departments of Granada, 
Carazo, Masaya, and Rivas. The entire area will be divided among 
67 private producers and 52 cooperatives. The ownership titles 
will benefit 874 heads of families and over 3,000 people, 
according to the article. 

