<H3> <TI>   The Netherlands Forgives $2 Million Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    The Netherlands Forgives $2 Million Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20705A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20705A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 15 April 
1994 on page 16 reports that the Netherlands has forgiven $2 
million of Nicaragua's $15-million debt. The Netherlands forgave 
more than half of Nicaragua's $38.5 million between 1991 and 
1993. The article reports that the Netherlands will contribute 
$1.3 million to the environment and energy sector in support of 
a geothermal project which will reduce Nicaragua's dependence on 
oil. The two countries are negotiationg a $20-million geothermal 
project to be financed by the Netherlands, according to the 
article. 

</TEXT>

