<H3> <TI>   Germany Funds Agricultural Project </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Germany Funds Agricultural Project </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20705E </F>
<F P=103> 94P20705E </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 19 April 
1994 on page 4 reports that the Integral Rural Development 
Program sponsored by the Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock 
(MAG) will convert farms and parcels of lands in Leon and 
Chinandega to more profitable units. The program, which will 
receive German Government financing, will introduce new crops, 
provide technical training and new technology, and will benefit 
1,950 families in 10 municipalities. MAG Minister Rondon noted 
that the program aims to reduce malnutrition, poverty, and 
unemployment in the region. Nicaragua will reportedly contribute 
$2 million for the first phase of the program, planned for 1995, 
while the German Technical Cooperation agency will provide $3 
million. 

</TEXT>

