<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Castro, Other Officials Arrive in Barbados </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Castro, Other Officials Arrive in Barbados </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0505011394 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0058 GMT 
5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0505011394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Commander in Chief Fidel Castro arrived on 4 
May in Bridgetown, Barbados, to attend the First International 
Small Island Nations Conference on Sustainable Development. 
Castro will participate in the high-level portion of the 
conference on 5-6 May. 
  President Castro traveled to Barbados in the company of 
Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, president of the National Assembly 
of the People's Government; Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina; 
and Environment Minister Rosa Elena Simeon, among other 
high-level officials. 

