<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Socialist Party To Support Lula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Socialist Party To Support Lula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0405190894 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 2 
May 94 p 1-7 </F>

<F P=103> PY0405190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Paulo Peixoto] </F>
  [Excerpt] The PPS [People's Socialist Party] yesterday 
decided to support the candidacy of PT [Workers Party] leader 
Luis Inacio Lula da Silva. 
  The party made the decision during a convention held over 
the 
weekend in Belo Horizonte (Minas Gerais). 
  The convention was attended by 74 of the 117 delegates with 
the right to vote. Of the 74, 69 voted in favor of the alliance. 
  There were four votes against, while one delegate abstained 
(he did not vote either for or against). 
  PPS Secretary General Francisco Almeida, 54, said the party 
will work to expand the front that supports Lula and 
"progressive parties." 
  The PPS does not want the campaign and Lula's program of 
government to become radical. 
  "We want a broad debate on the program. We will begin with 
the PT program, but it must be open to change, because new 
sectors should join in for the run-off election," he said. 
  The PPS will deliver its proposals to the PT in 15 days. 
  Of the PT factions, the PPS supports the one led by Sao 
Paulo 
Deputy Jose Genoino. 
  Almeida has said that the differences between the PPS and 
the 
PT "are not insurmountable." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

