<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0305212294 </F>
<F P=103> PA0305212294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic developments monitored through 3 May. 
  The National Institute of Statistics and Census (Inec) has 
reported prices rose this year by 3 percent in April, while in 
March they rose 2.64 percent. Inec added prices rose 3.6 
percent in April 1993. (Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 
GMT 2 May 94) 
  On 1 May, Agriculture Minister Mariano Gonzalez reported 
Ecuadoran banana exports surpassed 1 million tons in the first 4 
months of this year, which represents a record figure. The 
minister added that foreign currency revenue between 1 January 
and 15 April amounted to more than $123 million and that 54 
percent of the sales went to the countries of the European 
Union. (Madrid EFE in Spanish 2305 GMT 1 May 94) 

</TEXT>

