<H3> <TI>   Barbados Minister on Castro Presence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Barbados Minister on Castro Presence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0505233694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1934 GMT 
5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0505233694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Barbados Foreign Minister Branford Taitt stated to 
PRENSA LATINA that the presence of Cuban President Fidel Castro 
at the First International Small Island [Nations] Conference has 
greatly contributed to defining the objectives and strategies of 
the conference. 
  Following a brief meeting with Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto 
Robaina, Taitt said he had been excited to learn that Fidel 
Castro was to attend the Bridgetown conference. Taitt pointed 
out that Fidel Castro's address to the plenum was brilliant, and 
that he personally believes Castro's presence lends greater 
importance to the conference and contributes to defining 
fundamental elements in the strategies of sustainable 
development of the small island nations. 
  Taitt added that the process of integrating Cuba into the 
Caribbean Community's economic mechanisms would not suffer 
delays due to external pressures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

