<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The two main parties that comprise the government 
coalition in Chile advocate official plans to increase ties of 
cooperation with Cuba. Gutenberg Martinez, president of the 
Christian Democratic Party, asserted that his organization has a 
positive view toward any effort that could signify solidarity 
with the Cuban people. 
  Socialist Party President Camilo Escalona expressed his 
belief that the upcoming Ibero-American Summit represents a good 
opportunity for Chile to substantiate its plan of cooperation 
with Cuba. 

