<H3> <TI>   Matanzas Electric Plant Maintenance Begins </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Matanzas Electric Plant Maintenance Begins </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0505021394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0505021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The workers of the modern Antonio Guiteras Electric 
Plant in Matanzas City will stop work tonight, following 124 
days of continuous operation of the 130-megawatt unit, to 
conduct a three-day maintenance program on the boiler. This was 
announced by plant manager Jesus Valdez Torra, who added that on 
this occasion there will be no need for support from other 
organizations and that the plant workers will undertake the 
maintenance program without problems, given that all the 
required parts are at hand. 
  With the shutdown at the Antonio Guiteras plant, the 
National 
Electric System will reduce its electric generation capacity by 
10 percent. This will be reflected in a slight outage increase. 
However, as soon as the gas circulator unit of the boiler is 
repaired, which is expected to be completed by 8 May, the unit 
will be ready to produce the 330 megawatts it regularly 
produces, with low fuel consumption and the highest efficiency 
to date in the electric sector. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

