<H3> <TI>   Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Killed 4 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Killed 4 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0505194994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0505194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have learned from a reliable source that 
Jean-Verdy Bastien, owner of the Celeste Borlette Banks and the 
private radio station Celeste FM, was assassinated on the night 
of 4 May at about 2200 in upper Delmas. His driver was also 
injured during the attack against him by a group of armed men 
who had set up an ambush. According to our source, Jean-Verdy 
Bastien's body was transported to the general hospital morgue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

