<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PT Candidate Explains Election Platform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PT Candidate Explains Election Platform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0505183694 </F>
<F P=103> PA0505183694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 26 Apr 94 reports that Labor Party [PT] 
presidential candidate Cecilia Soto explained her platform 
during Radio ACIR's "Panorama Newscast." She stated the 
Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI], National Action Party 
[PAN], and the Party of the Democratic Revolution [PRD] "share 
the obsolescence and fatigue of the Mexican political system." 
Commenting on PRI presidential candidate Ernesto Zedillo's 
invitation to his PRD and PAN rivals to hold a debate, she 
regrets her exclusion and adds that it breaks slain PRI 
candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio's promise that the debate would 
include all candidates. When describing what her cabinet would 
look like if she were elected, Soto says the country must have 
"true" experts in their fields. She adds that her cabinet would 
include members of other parties and several women. On the topic 
of the Federal Judicial Police, Soto advocates abolishing this 
corps as it has turned into "a Frankenstein monster that is 
difficult to control." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

