<H3> <TI>   PRD Official Denies Party Linked to Cuba </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRD Official Denies Party Linked to Cuba </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0505223694 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0505223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Telemetro Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] </F>
  [Text] PRD [Democratic Revolutionary Party] Secretary 
General Mitchel Doens has denied reports that his party is 
receiving support from the Cuban Government, as claimed by 
Molirena [Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement] legislator 
Leo Gonzalez. Doens said PRD members had previous knowledge 
about the document Gonzalez presented, which Doens described as 
a political gambit, and he announced that he will file slander 
complaints against the Molirena legislator in the Peace and 
Justice Commission and in the Electoral Tribunal. 
  [Begin Doens recording] The only thing I can say is that Mr. 
Gonzalez is a mouse who got caught in his own trap. A few weeks 
ago, we had this document in our possession because a friend in 
the government gave it to us. We immediately wrote a letter to 
the Justice and Peace Commission and delivered it to commission 
member Ms. Irene Perurena with the document Mr. Gonzalez 
yesterday brought to the Foreign Ministry. 
  Earlier, we talked with a top Cuban Embassy official to have 
him explain that document to us. We found the document to be 
completely false, considering it contains seven mistakes, 
including forged signatures of the officials who are allegedly 
in charge of directions at the Cuban Embassy and in Cuba. 
  Later, Cuban Charge d'Affaires Miguel Martinez delivered 
this 
document to the Foreign Ministry, before Mr. Gonzalez did, 
precisely because of the implications this could have on his 
diplomatic mission in the country. We can categorically say 
this is a political gambit that is part of the dirty propaganda 
tactics being used against our party. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

