<H3> <TI>   Government Convenes Constituent Assembly for 25 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Convenes Constituent Assembly for 25 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0505155394 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1202 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0505155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 5 May (NA) -- The PEN [National 
Executive Branch] has announced that the Constituent Convention 
will meet as of 0900 [1200 GMT] on 25 May. The executive branch 
asked the Entre Rios provincial government "to make all 
necessary arrangements for the meeting." 
  The call comes in Decree 657, which was published yesterday 
in the Official Gazette. The decree calls on "Constituent 
Assembly members elected on 10 April to meet in Parana, Entre 
Rios Province, at 0900 on 25 May 1994." 
  The decree is signed by President Carlos Menem and Interior 
Minister Carlos Ruckauf. It states that the call follows Law 
24309, which establishes that the Convention must open within 60 
days of the election. 
  The decree adds that the law declaring the need for 
reforming 
the Constitution "establishes that the Chamber of Deputies' 
internal regulation will regulate the Convention's operation" 
and that "due to the importance of the event, the opening date 
-- 25 May -- grants the occasion the necessary solemnity and 
importance because it coincides with another anniversary of our 
independence." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

