<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Franco Meets Angolan President Dos Santos </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Franco Meets Angolan President Dos Santos </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0605021194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2342 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0605021194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 3 May (EFE) -- Official sources reported 
that the presidents of Brazil and Angola, Itamar Franco and 
Eduardo dos Santos, met today in Brasilia. They discussed the 
Angolan civil war and Nelson Mandela's election as the new South 
African president. 
  Dos Santos, who has been visiting the resort of Ilheus, in 
Bahia State, for the last 15 days, paid Franco a courtesy visit. 
The two presidents analyzed the political situation of the 
southern African countries and other matters of common interest. 
  A presidential spokesman said: "It was an informal meeting 
between the presidents of two friendly countries." 
  Franco and Dos Santos evaluated the electoral victory of 
Mandela and of his party, the African National Congress. They 
considered this victory positive from the political point of 
view of Angola and the other countries of the southern region of 
the African continent. 
  The two presidents also exchanged ideas about the first 
summit of Portuguese-speaking countries, which will be held in 
Lisbon in June. The summit will be attended by the presidents 
and chiefs of state of Brazil, Portugal, Angola, Mozambique, 
Cape Verde, Guinea-Bissau, and Sao Tome and Principe. 

</TEXT>

