<H3> <TI>   Country Joins UN Genetic Engineering Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Country Joins UN Genetic Engineering Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0605035594 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 29 Apr 94 p C11 </F>
<F P=103> PY0605035594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Jose Maria Lopez Barajas] </F>
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- Chile's admission into the 
International Center for Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology 
(ICGEB) represents an important diplomatic achievement for the 
country. Chile was admitted during the meeting in which the 
ICGEB was created in Vienna this week. 
  Chile will be a member of the ICGEB Governors' Board. The 
ICGEB is a UN organization, and its main objective is to study 
and conduct research in agricultural and livestock genetics to 
improve production. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

