<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abreu Says No Withdrawal From Mercosur Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abreu Says No Withdrawal From Mercosur Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0605033294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2306 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0605033294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brasilia, 5 May (EFE) -- A Brazilian Foreign 
Ministry spokesperson told EFE today that Uruguayan Foreign 
Minister Sergio Abreu today guaranteed his Brazilian colleague, 
Celso Amorim, that Uruguay will not withdraw from the 
negotiations to establish the Common Market of the South 
(Mercosur) import tariffs. 
  Abreu got ahold of Amorim in Paris, where he is on an 
official visit, and during a telephone conversation denied a 
report published in Montevideo claiming that Uruguay had decided 
to withdraw from the negotiations due to disagreements over the 
Brazilian initiative to create a free trade zone in South 
America. 
  The Uruguayan delegation today continued its participation 
in 
Mercosur's Common Market Group, the main technical level for the 
integration mechanism, which is meeting this week in the 
Argentine capital. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

