<H3> <TI>   Electric Outages Scheduled for 5-6 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electric Outages Scheduled for 5-6 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0605120894 Havana Tele Rebelde Network in Spanish 2235 GMT 
5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0605120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Outages have been taking place due to the electric 
generation deficit of the National Electric System, mainly the 
shutdown for maintenance of the most powerful generator unit in 
Cuba, Matanzas' Antonio Guiteras plant. 
  Tonight from 1900 to 0000, outages are scheduled for 
Guanabacoa, Regla, Cotorro, San Miguel del Padron, Centro 
Habana, Habana Vieja, Habana del Este, Marianao, Playa, and La 
Lisa Municipalities as well as areas of other municipalities on 
the same circuits. 
  On 6 May, Friday, outages are scheduled for Marianao, Playa, 
La Lisa, Boyeros, 10 de Octubre, and Arroyo Naranjo 
Municipalities will experienced outages from 0500 to 0900 and 
from 1300 to 1900. Likewise, Centro Habana, Habana Vieja, Habana 
del Este, Plaza, Cerro, Guanabacoa, Regla, Cotorro, and San 
Miguel del Padron Municipalities will experience scheduled 
outages from 0900 to 1300 and from 1900 to 0000. This 
information was provided by Arturo Mora de la Cruz. 

</TEXT>

