<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aristide Asks For Renewal of UN/OAS Mandate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aristide Asks For Renewal of UN/OAS Mandate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0605191894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0605191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jean-Bertrand Aristide solicits the renewal of the 
mandate of the civilian mission in Haiti. In a letter addressed 
to the UN secretary general, the Haitian president-in-exile 
asked for the renewal of the mandate of the International 
Civilian Mission in Haiti, according to the terms of reference 
already negotiated with Dante Caputo. 
  Referring to a deterioration of human rights and democracy 
in 
Haiti, Aristide hoped that the presence of the mission is 
contributing to an improvement in the human rights situation and 
helping create a favorable environment for political dialogue in 
the country. 

</TEXT>

