<H3> <TI>   Rumors: Rightist Government Imminent; Malval Sought </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rumors: Rightist Government Imminent; Malval Sought </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0605193894 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0605193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Rumors indicating that right-wing political 
leaders are ready to install a new government, challenging the 
United Nations and U.S. President Bill Clinton, are circulating 
in the Haitian capital. The British news agency, Reuters, 
reports that Haitian businessmen are worried that the extreme 
right is about to install a new de facto government. They report 
that they [not further identified] have asked for the return of 
Robert Malval as prime minister, a post he left with disgust 
last December. They believe that having a legitimate leader in 
this post could fill the temporal vacuum and reduce the 
necessity to fill it. 
  Someone close to Malval refused to confirm or to deny the 
speculation, stating that any approach might be be considered. I 
cannot reject that, this official said. Depending on how it is 
presented, Malval would have to wait and see of what the offer 
consists. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

