<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Recontras Threaten Cardinal Obando, Esteli Bishop </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Recontras Threaten Cardinal Obando, Esteli Bishop </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0705203094 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1824 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0705203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 7 May (DPA) -- Charrito [Ciriaco Palacios] 
and Northiel [Wilfredo Gutierrez or Wilfredo Chavarria], two 
recontra leaders, have made death threats against Cardinal 
Miguel Obando y Bravo, Esteli Bishop Monsignor Juan Abelardo 
Mata, and parish priest Octaviano Rodriguez, Managua's morning 
newspaper LA TRIBUNA reported today. 
  According to the publication, the religious leaders were 
threatened because they favor the disarmament of the group of 
former rebels organized in the 3-80 Northern Front, which 
surrendered its weapons and returned to civilian society. 
  The bishop of Esteli, a city located more than 100 km north 
of Managua, said the armed groups "have been telling the 
peasants they are going to kill us because we helped El Chacal 
(Jose Angel Talavera, who was the leader of the 3-80 Northern 
Front) to demobilize." 
  The armed groups are being pursued by Army and police troops 
following an order by Nicaraguan President Violeta Chamorro to 
eradicate the armed gangs that have committed murders, 
robberies, and kidnappings. 
  Esteli Bishop Mata received death threats last year from the 
pro-Sandinist Peasant-Worker Revolutionary Front (FROC). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

